div.p:
The Defense Program Review Committee has completed a review of our military
                    strategy and planning for Asia in the aftermath of the Vietnam war. The study
                    covered a full range of strategic questions and has recommended that guidance be
                    distributed on several issues. Four issues were considered ready for decision: 

— the broad objectives of Security Assistance planning for
                            Asia;

— basic strategic guidance for our conventional forces in Asia;

— our tactical nuclear planning;

— long term deployment planning.
